# GitTimes agent API — environment for systemd (gittimes-api.service).
# Copy to deploy/api.env on the VPS and fill in. NEVER commit the real file.
#   cp deploy/api.env.example deploy/api.env && $EDITOR deploy/api.env
#   sudo systemctl restart gittimes-api

# --- server ---
PORT=3717
HOST=127.0.0.1          # localhost-only; nginx terminates TLS and proxies. Never 0.0.0.0.

# --- x402 paywall ---
# Setting X402_RECEIVER is the single switch that turns the paywall ON.
# Leave it unset to keep every endpoint free.
X402_RECEIVER=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000   # <-- dedicated Git Times Base wallet
X402_NETWORK=base                                           # base | base-sepolia (test)
X402_PRICE_USDC=0.01                                        # price per paid call
X402_MODE=facilitator                                       # facilitator | sim(tests only) | off

# --- settlement via Coinbase CDP (chosen path: fee-free on Base, sponsors gas) ---
# One-time on the box:  npm install @coinbase/cdp-sdk
# Get a free API key at https://portal.cdp.coinbase.com. When these two are set,
# the API auto-targets the CDP facilitator and signs each request with a JWT —
# no wallet private key on this box, gas paid by CDP.
CDP_API_KEY_ID=                                             # CDP API key id
CDP_API_KEY_SECRET=                                         # CDP API key secret (NEVER log/expose)
# X402_FACILITATOR_URL=https://api.cdp.coinbase.com/platform/v2/x402   # implied by CDP keys; override only to switch providers

# --- alternative: keyless / self-hosted facilitator (no CDP) ---
# Leave the CDP keys empty and point at a mainnet-capable facilitator instead
# (e.g. PayAI, or a self-hosted x402.rs). Optional static bearer:
# X402_FACILITATOR_URL=https://facilitator.example.com
# X402_FACILITATOR_KEY=                                     # static bearer, if that facilitator needs one
# X402_VERSION=1                                            # x402 protocol version advertised (default 1)
